Return a newly allocated pair whose car is @vari{obj} and whose cdr is
@varii{obj}.  The pair is guaranteed to be different (in the sense of
@func{eqv?}) from every existing object.

@example
(cons 'a '())           =>  (a)
(cons '(a) '(b c d))    =>  ((a) b c d)
(cons "a" '(b c))       =>  ("a" b c)
(cons 'a 3)             =>  (a . 3)
(cons '(a b) 'c)        =>  ((a b) . c)
@end example
@end deffn


